More Anxiety

Even the Emiratis=E2=80=99 cash, which can=E2=80=99t come soon enough, won=
=E2=80=99t necessarily fix Sotheby=E2=80=99s problems. The house=E2=80=99s =
new fee structure is still unproven. Yes, lowering the buyer=E2=80=99s prem=
ium should be good for consignors, especially since the old fees could add =
as much as 35 percent (along with sales tax) to the hammer price. But even =
if this was the right decision=E2=80=94and executives inside Christie=E2=80=
=99s and Phillips are certainly trying to convince plenty of sellers that i=
t wasn=E2=80=99t=E2=80=94Sotheby=E2=80=99s would have been wiser to time th=
e transition to when its financial position was stronger and the market was=
 on the upswing.

Last week, as I previously noted, the New York mid-season sales were pretty=
 much comparable between Sotheby=E2=80=99s and Christie=E2=80=99s. Sotheby=
=E2=80=99s sold $33 million worth of art in New York; Christie=E2=80=99s so=
ld $29.9 million today.
Though Sotheby=E2=80=99s did have a much better hammer ratio for their sale=
s, which could validate their pitch for the new fees even though, as I was =
reminded by a longtime auction watcher, much of the property in those sales=
 had been held over from previous auctions. They were the smaller lots from=
 the bigger estate sales that had nowhere else to be sold.

The catalogs for the Frieze sales in London next week tell a different stor=
y. Sotheby=E2=80=99s has =C2=A334 million in presale value in its London ev=
ening sale; Christie=E2=80=99s has =C2=A373 million, more than twice as muc=
h. In the contemporary day sales, it=E2=80=99s =C2=A34 million at Sotheby=
=E2=80=99s and =C2=A311 million at Christie=E2=80=99s, an even greater disp=
arity.

Is this a sign that the new fee structure is holding back consignments? Tru=
thfully, there are many factors that could explain the disparity, including=
 the decline of the London market and Sotheby=E2=80=99s previous decision t=
o move more resources to Paris. But, alas, those figures
don=E2=80=99t combat the impression among art advisors and rival houses=E2=
=80=94not to mention current and former employees=E2=80=94that Sotheby=E2=
=80=99s is in the middle of a skid.

