          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 16px;">
           <p style=3D"margin: 0; color: #000000; font-size: 16px; line-hei=
ght: 30px; margin-top: 20px; margin-bottom: 0;">Welcome back to Wall Power,=
 your twice-weekly report on the art market. I=E2=80=99m <b>Marion Maneker<=
/b>.<br/><br/>The slow-simmering Sotheby=E2=80=99s story has suddenly begun=
 to boil. <i>The Wall Street Journal</i>=E2=80=99s prominent piece last wee=
k alluded to a cash crunch at the auction house=E2=80=94with surprisingly l=
ittle to back up the claim. Of course, that moved the company=E2=80=99s dwi=
ndling cash position from an offstage saga to a starring role. Now, consign=
ors, creditors, and employees, both current and former, are on high alert. =
Will Sotheby=E2=80=99s get its essential cash infusion in time to save the =
all-important November sales? What=E2=80=99s going on with the much-touted=
=E2=80=94but now oft-second-guessed=E2=80=94acquisition of the Breuer build=
ing? If the Emiratis can=E2=80=99t or won=E2=80=99t close, would a bridge f=
inancing be necessary? If so, who might step up?<br/><br/>I=E2=80=99ll give=
 you my
thoughts on all of that, below. <br/><br/><i>But first=E2=80=A6</i><br/><br=
/></p><ul style=3D"margin:0;color:#000000;font-size:16px;line-height:30px;m=
argin-top:0;margin-bottom:0;list-style-type:square;mso-special-format:bulle=
t"><li><i>Christie=E2=80=99s Post-War to Present results:</i> Christie=E2=
=80=99s posted a weak $30.5 million sale for its mid-season opener. The ham=
mer ratio was .85 and the sell-through rate a low 74 percent. Much of the p=
roperty was held over from larger estates sold in previous years. Even so, =
there were strong performances for <b>Lois Dodd</b>, <b>August=C3=ADn C=C3=
=A1rdenas</b>, <b>Ruth Asawa</b>, <b>Louise Nevelson</b>, <b>Claire Taboure=
t</b>, <b>Bisa Butler</b>, <b>Cynthia Hawkins</b>, <b>Lynne Mapp Drexler</b=
>,<b> Robert Motherwell</b>,<b> Ed Ruscha</b>, and <b>Bob Thompson</b>, amo=
ng others.  </li></ul>
