          <td style=3D"padding-bottom: 36px; color: #000000; font-size: 16p=
x; line-height: 30px; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 0;">The problem Sotheby=
=E2=80=99s faces is that ex-employees, like the ones gathered at Redden=E2=
=80=99s memorial, are busy spinning up different scenarios to explain the E=
miratis=E2=80=99 foot-dragging, and as you can imagine, none of them is goo=
d. At the same time, there=E2=80=99s been a real talent drain, with a long =
summer of departures including the principal auctioneer in Hong Kong, the v=
ice chairman for institutional sales, the S.V.P. of global proposals, the h=
ead of African and Oceanic art, the head of Sotheby=E2=80=99s Zurich, the h=
ead of client strategy in the Americas, and the global head of dispute reso=
lution. In the past few weeks, some key support staff also left the company=
, demoralizing many of the specialists who liked them personally and would =
have relied upon them in the coming months of high-profile sales. <br/><br/=
>Speculation surrounds the C-suite, too. The
news last month that Sotheby=E2=80=99s C.F.O. <b>Jean-Luc Berrebi</b>, one =
of Drahi=E2=80=99s most trusted executives, would be <u><a href=3D"https://=
email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dTU3l1YmY0QXV=
mdmxPOFRxVDB1RT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9wdWNrLm5ld3MvY2FuLXBhdHJpY2stZHJhaG=
ktbWFpbnRhaW4tY29udHJvbC1vZi1zb3RoZWJ5cy8_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVdhbGwrUG93ZXIrL=
StTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMCUyRjElMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb250ZW50PVdhbGwrUG93=
ZXIrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxMCUyRjElMkYyNCUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWx=
fYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MDAyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNj=
E3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6M=
TA0Njc2N30/01a61ad05298d390c8dbd74896f55e2f899df85e4b2ba4c5537b065f0eb6f172=
" style=3D"color:#d40000;text-decoration:none;font-weight:bold" class=3D"sd=
f">stepping down</a></u> set off speculation about the fate of C.E.O. <b>Ch=
arlie</b> <b>Stewart</b>. (Many Drahi watchers point out that he likes to m=
ove his executives around.) But Stewart has been the face of Sotheby=E2=80=
=99s for some time now, and he is intimately associated with the new fee st=
ructure and the company=E2=80=99s investments, especially in real estate. H=
e also collaborated on a long profile with ARTnews that was recently publis=
hed in its Top 200 Collectors issue. That=E2=80=99s hardly the sign of an e=
xecutive getting ready for a move. <br/><br/>Finally, of course, there is t=
he much-discussed fate of the
Breuer building. Sotheby=E2=80=99s maintains the deal on the building was a=
lways slated to close some time this fall. But the longer it takes, the mor=
e people start wondering whether <b>Larry Gagosian</b>=E2=80=94who has to m=
ove out of his flagship gallery location nearby=E2=80=94will somehow swoop =
in and buy the building out from under Drahi. The Breuer, home of the Whitn=
ey Museum from 1966 to 2014, lacks a loading dock, which is kind of a probl=
em for anyone putting on a high volume of shows. As a piece of commercial r=
eal estate, though, it=E2=80=99s not really valuable to anyone but Drahi or=
 Gagosian. (For some, Gagosian would be in a better position to utilize the=
 space throughout the year.) <br/><br/>I may have been watching way too muc=
h of HBO=E2=80=99s <i>Industry</i>, but the Machiavellian part of my brain =
sometimes half wonders if the Emiratis are not playing out some melodramati=
c plot where they push Sotheby=E2=80=99s to the brink by delaying the payme=
nt only to swoop in and buy it all on the cheap.
If I were writing this for <i>Industry</i>, I=E2=80=99d contemplate someone=
 like <b>Alexander</b> <b>Klabin</b>, the former hedge fund manager lurking=
 quietly on Sotheby=E2=80=99s cap table with a small ownership stake, also =
putting in a bid. And, of course, there are the former suitors who lost out=
 to Drahi that might reemerge to make a run at the trophy property. <br/><b=
r/>But as much as I think it would greatly help Sotheby=E2=80=99s for the E=
miratis or Drahi to do something definitive to rebuild confidence, like clo=
se on the Breuer building or announce some sort of bridge loan until the de=
al closes, I suspect everything will continue to muddle through until the p=
layers turn over their final cards.<br/></td>
